    "created_at": "2014-05-15T20:45:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-15T20:45:28Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "From in-person review:\n- replace `system` boolean with string `prefix`, so a normal system-wide install would be with `--prefix=/usr/local`, and an apt package might do `--prefix=/usr`\n- load kernel specs from both `/usr/share` and `/usr/local/share`, to accommodate system-managed and user-managed system-wide installs\n- do not make the system-wide kernel paths configurable for loading\n"
  },
